alibre/LifeHacker--Wed--25-Aug-2021----/feed_0/article_13/images/img6_u3.jpg\"></p></div></span></p><div><p>Photo: Vlad Ispas (Shutterstock)</p></div></div><p>Waze will show you better routes if you’ve set the correct vehicle type in the app. Open Waze and go to <strong>Settings &gt; Vehicle details &gt; Vehicle type</strong> and select the correct one. This is particularly useful if you’re on a motorcycle because you’ll get faster routes that may not necessarily be suitable for cars.<br></p></div><div><div contenteditable=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"900\" data-id=\"74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97\" data-lightbox=\"true\" data-recommend-id=\"image://74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-width=\"1600\" draggable=\"false\"><p><span><div><p><img alt=\"Image for article titled 11 Wonderful Waze Settings Everyone Should Be Using\" data-alt=\"Image for article titled 11 Wonderful Waze Settings Everyone Should Be Using\" data-anim-src=\"\" data-chomp-id=\"74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97\" data-format=\"png\" data-srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,fl_progressive,g_center,h_80,pg_1,q_80,w_80/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 80w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_140/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 140w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_265/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 265w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_340/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 340w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_490/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 490w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_645/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 645w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_740/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 740w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_965/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 965w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1165/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 1165w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1315/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 1315w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1465/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 1465w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1600/74bbf2964f36f8b9f5f388cb1b2aed97.png 1600w\" draggable=\"auto\" sizes=\"     (max-width: 25em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (max-width: 37.31em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (min-width: 37.37em) and (max-width: 49.94em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em) 800px,     (min-width: 63.75em) and (max-width: 85.19em) calc(66.5vw - 32px),     800px    \" src=\"/calibre/LifeHacker--Wed--25-Aug-2021----/feed_0/article_13/images/img7.png\"></p></div></span></p></div><p>If you frequent toll roads in the U.S., Canada, or Israel, you can add your toll passes to Waze. This will allow Waze to send you through dedicated lanes for these passes to save you some hassle. Waze also shows you toll rates and prompts you to add a pass for certain toll gates when you’re planning a route.<br></p><p>You can add toll or HOV passes in Waze by going to <strong>Settings &gt; Vehicle details &gt; Toll &amp; HOV passes &gt; Show all</strong>.</p></div><div><div contenteditable=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"shutterstock\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"3258\" data-id=\"b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1\" data-lightbox=\"true\" data-recommend-id=\"image://b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-width=\"5777\" draggable=\"false\"><p><span><div><p><img alt=\"Image for article titled 11 Wonderful Waze Settings Everyone Should Be Using\" data-alt=\"Image for article titled 11 Wonderful Waze Settings Everyone Should Be Using\" data-anim-src=\"\" data-chomp-id=\"b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,fl_progressive,g_center,h_80,pg_1,q_80,w_80/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 80w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_140/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 140w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_265/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 265w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_340/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 340w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_490/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 490w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_645/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 645w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_740/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 740w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_965/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 965w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1165/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 1165w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1315/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 1315w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1465/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 1465w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1600/b9d3ffa4c4dd9e3bd52362a50b47daa1.jpg 1600w\" draggable=\"auto\" sizes=\"     (max-width: 25em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (max-width: 37.31em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (min-width: 37.37em) and (max-width: 49.94em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em) 800px,     (min-width: 63.75em) and (max-width: 85.19em) calc(66.5vw - 32px),     800px    \" src=\"/calibre/LifeHacker--Wed--25-Aug-2021----/feed_0/article_13/images/img8_u2.jpg\"></p></div></span></p><div><p>Photo: Warith82 (Shutterstock)</p></div></div><p>Changing the music is one of the more annoying things to do while you’re driving, and Waze has made this easier by integrating the audio player in the map. When you’re navigating, you can hit the music icon to control the audio player easily. You can go to Waze <strong>Settings &gt; Audio player</strong> and check if your favorite services are available. Click <strong>Install</strong> next to the service of your choice. By default, Spotify, Audible, and YouTube Music are already installed, but unfortunately, Apple Music isn’t supported yet.</p></div><div><div contenteditable=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"shutterstock\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"2214\" data-id=\"287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d\" data-lightbox=\"true\" data-recommend-id=\"image://287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-width=\"3944\" draggable=\"false\"><p><span><div><p><img alt=\"Image for article titled 11 Wonderful Waze Settings Everyone Should Be Using\" data-alt=\"Image for article titled 11 Wonderful Waze Settings Everyone Should Be Using\" data-anim-src=\"\" data-chomp-id=\"287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,fl_progressive,g_center,h_80,pg_1,q_80,w_80/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 80w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_140/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 140w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_265/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 265w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_340/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 340w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_490/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 490w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_645/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 645w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_740/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 740w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_965/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 965w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1165/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 1165w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1315/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 1315w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1465/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 1465w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1600/287bcc1e825488941236f3b03406649d.jpg 1600w\" draggable=\"auto\" sizes=\"     (max-width: 25em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (max-width: 37.31em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (min-width: 37.37em) and (max-width: 49.94em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em) 800px,     (min-width: 63.75em) and (max-width: 85.19em) calc(66.5vw - 32px),     800px    \" src=\"/calibre/LifeHacker--Wed--25-Aug-2021----/feed_0/article_13/images/img9_u2.jpg\"></p></div></span></p><div><p>Photo: dennizn (Shutterstock)</p></div></div><p>Too many alerts and icons can get a bit overwhelming on Waze, so it’s great that you can customize and limit the number of things you see. To do it, open Waze and go to <strong>Settings &gt; Map display &gt; Reports</strong> and get rid of the things you don’t need. You can also go back to Map display settings and disable <strong>Show Wazers</strong> to hide other Waze users from the map.<br></p></div><div><div contenteditable=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"900\" data-id=\"8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc\" data-lightbox=\"true\" data-recommend-id=\"image://8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-width=\"1600\" draggable=\"false\"><p><span><div><p><img alt=\"Image for article titled 11 Wonderful Waze Settings Everyone Should Be Using\" data-alt=\"Image for article titled 11 Wonderful Waze Settings Everyone Should Be Using\" data-anim-src=\"\" data-chomp-id=\"8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc\" data-format=\"png\" data-srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,fl_progressive,g_center,h_80,pg_1,q_80,w_80/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 80w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_140/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 140w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_265/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 265w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_340/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 340w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_490/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 490w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_645/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 645w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_740/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 740w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_965/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 965w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1165/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 1165w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1315/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 1315w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1465/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 1465w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1600/8c5b5f5c7c6fea79ac5dcd7725b31efc.png 1600w\" draggable=\"auto\" sizes=\"     (max-width: 25em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (max-width: 37.31em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (min-width: 37.37em) and (max-width: 49.94em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em) 800px,     (min-width: 63.75em) and (max-width: 85.19em) calc(66.5vw - 32px),     800px    \" src=\"/calibre/LifeHacker--Wed--25-Aug-2021----/feed_0/article_13/images/img10.png\"></p></div></span></p></div><p>Waze allows you to change the icon of your vehicle. You can go to <strong>Settings &gt; Map display &gt; Car icon</strong> and select what you like. The default is an arrow icon, but you can change it to a motorbike, car, bus, truck, or even a race car.<br></p></div><div><div contenteditable=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"900\" data-id=\"6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c\" data-lightbox=\"true\" data-recommend-id=\"image://6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-width=\"1600\" draggable=\"false\"><p><span><div><p><img alt=\"Image for article titled 11 Wonderful Waze Settings Everyone Should Be Using\" data-alt=\"Image for article titled 11 Wonderful Waze Settings Everyone Should Be Using\" data-anim-src=\"\" data-chomp-id=\"6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c\" data-format=\"png\" data-srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,fl_progressive,g_center,h_80,pg_1,q_80,w_80/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 80w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_140/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 140w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_265/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 265w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_340/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 340w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_490/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 490w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_645/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 645w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_740/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 740w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_965/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 965w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1165/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 1165w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1315/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 1315w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1465/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 1465w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1600/6c2763d31ee814724b2abfd78749294c.png 1600w\" draggable=\"auto\" sizes=\"     (max-width: 25em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (max-width: 37.31em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (min-width: 37.37em) and (max-width: 49.94em) calc(100vw - 32px),     (min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em) 800px,     (min-width: 63.75em) and (max-width: 85.19em) calc(66.5vw - 32px),     800px    \" src=\"/calibre/LifeHacker--Wed--25-Aug-2021----/feed_0/article_13/images/img11.png\"></p></div></span></p></div><p>If you’re in the habit of forgetting things at the end of your drive, you can set up helpful Waze reminders to make things easier. While Waze calls this feature a Child reminder, you can use it for anything you like. It’s good to check if you’ve left someone or something important in the car—such as an infant, keys, documents, or simply if you’ve switched off the engine and locked the car.<br></p><p>You can set these reminders up in Waze by going to <strong>Settings &gt; Reminders &gt; Child reminder</strong> and enabling <strong>Show reminder</strong>. Tap <strong>Custom message</strong> to customize this reminder.</p></div>\n</div>",
  "textContent": "Photo: Din Mohd Yaman (Shutterstock)Google’s got the navigation app market locked down tight, owning two of the most popular navigation apps for Android and iPhone. Google Maps has lots of excellent features and is pre-loaded on Android phones sold in most places around the world, but in spite of that, Waze has a cult following in several countries, including the U.S.There are lots of people who prefer Waze over Google Maps, and it’s easy to see why—it’s essentially Google Maps with personality. It also has several great features that you should check out. Here are some of the best.Photo: Najmi Arif (Shutterstock)Waze ships with a built-in speedometer that is extremely useful. It shows you how fast you’re going and it can alert you when you’re over or below the speed limit. (Rachel would’ve loved to have Waze in Friends season 7, episode 23.)Open Waze and go to Settings > Speedometer > Show speed limit and set it to Always. This will show the speed limit on the map. Then go back to the Speedometer settings page and enable Alert when speeding for Waze to let you know when you’re above the limit.Why keep a boring Waze voice when you’ve got so many fun options? If you’re tired of the neutral navigation assistant, go to Waze Settings > Voice and sound and check your options. The English voice has many options such as PAW Patrol, Boy George, and Master Chief from Halo so you can have a good laugh while navigating to your destination.If you’re feeling adventurous, you can even record your own voice and set it as the default on Waze. Under Voice and sound settings, tap Record new voice, and have fun.Photo: Mohd Syis Zulkipli (Shutterstock)One of the things Waze doesn’t make obvious is how to find alternative routes, but that option appears before you start the trip. After you’ve set a destination, tap the Routes option and go to the Map view tab to view alternatives and choose the one that works best for you.Photo: David Orsoazurri (Shutterstock)Keep using Waze for a while and you’ll begin to see trip suggestions. This is Waze finding spots you may be interested in and suggesting that you go check these out. Trip suggestions appear above the ETA bar in Waze, and you’ll be able to swipe through cards to explore these suggestions.Photo: dennizn (Shutterstock)When you’re using Waze, an orange icon will appear on the map. This is the Report button, which you can use to report any errors or hazards to others who use the app. Before you start your trip, you can look up community reports to see if there are any unexpected delays on the route.Photo: Vlad Ispas (Shutterstock)Waze will show you better routes if you’ve set the correct vehicle type in the app. Open Waze and go to Settings > Vehicle details > Vehicle type and select the correct one. This is particularly useful if you’re on a motorcycle because you’ll get faster routes that may not necessarily be suitable for cars.If you frequent toll roads in the U.S., Canada, or Israel, you can add your toll passes to Waze. This will allow Waze to send you through dedicated lanes for these passes to save you some hassle. Waze also shows you toll rates and prompts you to add a pass for certain toll gates when you’re planning a route.You can add toll or HOV passes in Waze by going to Settings > Vehicle details > Toll & HOV passes > Show all.Photo: Warith82 (Shutterstock)Changing the music is one of the more annoying things to do while you’re driving, and Waze has made this easier by integrating the audio player in the map. When you’re navigating, you can hit the music icon to control the audio player easily. You can go to Waze Settings > Audio player and check if your favorite services are available. Click Install next to the service of your choice. By default, Spotify, Audible, and YouTube Music are already installed, but unfortunately, Apple Music isn’t supported yet.Photo: dennizn (Shutterstock)Too many alerts and icons can get a bit overwhelming on Waze, so it’s great that you can customize and limit the number of things you see. To do it, open Waze and go to Settings > Map display > Reports and get rid of the things you don’t need. You can also go back to Map display settings and disable Show Wazers to hide other Waze users from the map.Waze allows you to change the icon of your vehicle. You can go to Settings > Map display > Car icon and select what you like. The default is an arrow icon, but you can change it to a motorbike, car, bus, truck, or even a race car.If you’re in the habit of forgetting things at the end of your drive, you can set up helpful Waze reminders to make things easier. While Waze calls this feature a Child reminder, you can use it for anything you like. It’s good to check if you’ve left someone or something important in the car—such as an infant, keys, documents, or simply if you’ve switched off the engine and locked the car.You can set these reminders up in Waze by going to Settings > Reminders > Child reminder and enabling Show reminder. Tap Custom message to customize this reminder.\n",
